STEP 1: Create Custom Object
Go to: Setup → Object Manager → Create → Custom Object
Fill:
Field	Value
Label	Employee
Plural Label	Employees
Object Name	Employee
Click:Save

✅ STEP 2: Create Fields
Inside Employee Object create:
Field Name	Type
Employee ID	Number
Department	Text
Salary	Number

✅ STEP 3: Create Tab
Go to: Setup → Tabs
Under: Custom Object Tabs
Click: New
Select: Employee
Choose any style → Next → Next → Save

✅ STEP 4: Open Employee Tab
Click: App Launcher (9 dots)

Search: Employee
Open Employee tab.

✅ STEP 5: Open Developer Console
⚙️ Gear Icon → Developer Console

✅ STEP 6: Run Apex Code
Go:Debug → Open Execute Anonymous Window

Paste:
Employee__c e = new Employee__c();

e.Name = 'Rahul Sharma';
e.Employee_ID__c = 101;
e.Department__c = 'IT';
e.Salary__c = 50000;
insert e;
System.debug('Employee Record Inserted Successfully');

Click:Execute

✅ STEP 7: Show Output
Go back to:
Employee Tab
Refresh page.
New employee record appears ✅